@MatsL (and everyone else that's hasn't already) : to get the idea - spend a while here: https://www.iiot.university/iiot-mini-course

This is the world as we live it.

@Joshua Stover Thank you!  I am using Chapt-GPT for python code development.  The main goal is to abstract the various instruments into a data model that can be parsed by type of sensor based on classification, temperature, pressure, and gas composition support.  I am building a library of sensors which includes the specifications and installation methods required to support Class 1 Div II Group A, B, C, D and note if the installation supports Non-incendive or explosion proof ratings in order to avoid the use of Intrinsically Safe Barriers.  Chat-GPT is helping me to build the database, data model, and viewer.  I would like to use the Model > View > Controller method with one service using python as the Controller for data validation and retrieval.  A separate python service using Flask as the viewer.  A separate service running mysql or postrgress to support the data storage.  I want to build my own API for this service using mkdocs and following the PEP8 documentation standard so the comments in the format of restructured text can dynamically build the API.  Chat-GPT has given me all of the code and information for this which is absolutely freaking insane.  

AI Personal Assistant: I am using Midjourney to create pictures of virtual assistants.  Chat-GPT to create tone specific responses in text.  ElevenLabs to convert that text to freakishly realistic audio, and https://www.d-id.com/ to upload the picture and audio to create a portrait video response.  

Example pictures from Midjourney, which are 100% made up, are shown and the sample introduction video.
